      "content": "# CloudScale API: User Profile Endpoint Guide\n## 1. Introduction\nThis document provides a comprehensive technical overview of the `GET /user` endpoint within the CloudScale REST architecture.\n### 1.1 Scope and Objectives\nThe primary objective is to securely retrieve authenticated user profile data without exposing sensitive PII beyond necessary scope.\n#### 1.2 Target Audience\nThis guide is intended for backend engineers, API consumers, and security auditors.\n##### 1.3 Prerequisites\nConsumers must possess a valid OAuth2 access token with the `read:user` scope.\n###### 1.4 Document Structure\nThe following sections detail authentication, response schemas, error handling, and integration patterns.\n####### 1.5 Version History\n| Version | Date | Changes |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| v1.0.0 | 2023-10-01 | Initial release |\n| v1.1.0 | 2023-11-15 | Added `last_login` field |\n######## 1.6 Related Documentation\nSee `POST /user/update` for profile modification procedures.\n######## 1",
